```java
static Document parseByteData(ByteBuffer byteData, String charsetName, String baseUri, Parser parser) {
    String docData;
    Document doc = null;

    // Determine charset if not provided
    if (charsetName == null) {
        // Decode using the default charset (UTF-8)
        docData = Charset.forName(defaultCharset).decode(byteData).toString();
        doc = parser.parseInput(docData, baseUri);

        // Look for <meta> tags to find the charset
        Element meta = doc.select("meta[http-equiv=content-type], meta[charset]").first();
        if (meta != null) {
            String foundCharset = null;

            if (meta.hasAttr("http-equiv")) {
                foundCharset = getCharsetFromContentType(meta.attr("content"));
            }
            // Check for charset attribute if not found in content type
            if (foundCharset == null && meta.hasAttr("charset")) {
                try {
                    foundCharset = meta.attr("charset");
                    if (!Charset.isSupported(foundCharset)) {
                        foundCharset = null;
                    }
                } catch (IllegalCharsetNameException e) {
                    foundCharset = null;
                }
            }

            // If a valid charset is found, re-decode
            if (foundCharset != null && !foundCharset.equals(defaultCharset)) {
                charsetName = foundCharset.trim().replaceAll("[\"']", "");
                byteData.rewind();
                docData = Charset.forName(charsetName).decode(byteData).toString();
                doc = null; // Reset document to parse again
            }
        }
    } else { // charset specified by user
        Validate.notEmpty(charsetName, "Must set charset arg to character set of file to parse. Set to null to attempt to detect from HTML");
        docData = Charset.forName(charsetName).decode(byteData).toString();
    }

    // Handle UTF-8 BOM
    if (docData.length() > 0 && docData.charAt(0) == 65279) {
        byteData.rewind();
        docData = Charset.forName(defaultCharset).decode(byteData).toString();
        docData = docData.substring(1); // Remove the BOM
        charsetName = defaultCharset; // Set charset to default
    }

    // Parse the document if it wasn't already parsed
    if (doc == null) {
        doc = parser.parseInput(docData, baseUri);
        doc.outputSettings().charset(charsetName);
    }

    return doc;
}
```

### Key Fixes:
1. **Character Calculation**: Corrected the logic to handle character set detection and decoding correctly.
2. **BOM Handling**: Ensured that the UTF-8 BOM is processed and handled correctly by using `substring` after detecting it.
3. **Charset Support Check**: Added a check to confirm that the charset is supported before using it for decoding.
4. **Re-declaration of Document**: Ensured that if the document needs to be parsed again (after a charset change), the document variable is reset to null.

This function should now handle character encoding and parsing more reliably.

